The snap command lets you install, configure, refresh and remove snaps.
Snaps are packages that work across many different Linux distributions,
enabling secure delivery and operation of the latest apps and utilities.

Usage: snap <command> [<options>...]

Commands can be classified as follows:


  Basics (basic snap management):
    find            Buscar paquetes para instalar
    info            Mostrar información detallada sobre los snaps
    install         Install snaps on the system
    list            Listar snaps instalados
    remove          Remove snaps from the system

  ...more (slightly more advanced snap management):
    refresh         Refresh snaps in the system
    revert          Revierte el snap dado a su estado previo
    switch          Cambia el snap a un canal diferente
    disable         Desactivar un snap en el sistema
    enable          Activar un snap en el sistema

  History (manage system change transactions):
    changes         Listar cambios de sistema
    tasks           Listar tareas de cambio
    abort           Abortar un cambio pendiente
    watch           Observar un cambio en progreso

  Daemons (manage services):
    services        Consultar el estado de los servicios
    start           Iniciar servicios
    stop            Detener servicios
    restart         Reiniciar servicios
    logs            Retrieve logs for services

  Commands (manage aliases):
    alias           Configurar un alias manual
    aliases         Listar aliases en el sistema
    unalias         Remove a manual alias, or the aliases for an entire snap
    prefer          Enable aliases from a snap, disabling any conflicting aliases

  Configuration (system administration and configuration):
    get             Imprimir opciones de configuración
    set             Cambiar las opciones de configuración
    wait            Wait for configuration

  Account (authentication to snapd and the snap store):
    login           Autentificar en snapd y en la tienda
    logout          Cerrar sesión en snapd y en la tienda
    whoami          Show the email the user is logged in with

  Permissions (manage permissions):
    connections     List interface connections
    interfaces      List interfaces' slots and plugs
    interface       Show details of snap interfaces
    connect         Conectar un enchufe a una ranura
    disconnect      Desconectar un enchufe de una ranura

  Snapshots (archives of snap data):
    saved           List currently stored snapshots
    save            Save a snapshot of the current data
    check-snapshot  Check a snapshot
    restore         Restore a snapshot
    forget          Delete a snapshot

  Other (miscellanea):
    version         Mostrar detalles de la versión
    warnings        List warnings
    okay            Acknowledge warnings
    ack             Añadir una afirmación al sistema
    known           Mostrar afirmaciones conocidas del tipo proporcionado

  Development (developer-oriented features):
    run             Ejecutar la orden snap dada
    pack            Empaquetar el directorio dado como un snap
    try             Test an unpacked snap in the system
    download        Descargar el snap dado
    prepare-image   Prepare a device image

For more information about a command, run 'snap help <command>'.
For a short summary of all commands, run 'snap help --all'.
